#Text=The Phoenix Suns ( 12 - 16 ) defeated the New Orleans Pelicans ( 7 - 19 ) 104 - 88 on Friday in a game with very little energy .
#Text=This was the case of two teams going through the motions and playing with very little energy .
#Text=It 's unclear if it was the team 's lack of success or whether you could hear a pin drop in the stadium , but there was just no energy in the arena .
#Text=The shooting really killed the Pelicans , as they went just 4 - for - 22 from three - point range .
#Text=In what was anticipated to be a high - scoring game , the two teams really struggled on both ends .
#Text=Phoenix took a 28 - 17 lead in the first quarter and it wasn’t really a game after that .
#Text=The Pelicans are hard to watch right now .
#Text=Their defense is one of the worst in the NBA and their offense had no rhythm tonight .
#Text=They shot just 36 percent from the field and 18 percent from long distance .
#Text=When the offense is playing like this with how bad their defense is , it 's nearly impossible for the Pelicans to win .
#Text=New Orleans ' best player on the night was Anthony Davis , who collected 16 points and 12 rebounds .
#Text=Eric Gordon shot the team out of the game , as he was just 2 - for - 11 from the field and 2 - for - 19 from three - point range in the loss .
#Text=The bench is major strength for this team , but they accumulated just 36 points on the evening , which included some garbage time scoring .
#Text=They 'll look to bounce - back against the Denver Nuggets on Sunday in their next game .
#Text=The Suns shot 52 percent in the game and took advantage of a bad defense .
#Text=They continued to get in the paint all night and scored 52 points in the paint .
#Text=Eric Bledsoe has another great game , as he tallied 29 points , nine assists , five rebounds and two steals in the win .
#Text=Alex Len also played well off the bench , as he amassed 19 points and 13 rebounds en route to a double - double .
#Text=What Phoenix will like most about this win is the defense , as they have been terrible defensively all season .
#Text=The Suns will host the Milwaukee Bucks on Sunday in their next matchup .
